      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHREWD ETHICS (6) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing sixth (19.99) in a Grade 4 at Bulli. Has good early speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Can bounce back. MARG'S VOGUE (4) had the drop on the lead and went on to be beaten 6 lengths into third (23.23) at The Gardens in a Grade 4/5 over 400m. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Expecting another good run. LITTLE BIT SUPER (3) has a strong record this trip with 12 wins and 12 placings from 35 starts. Was out of placings last time (20.09) at Grafton in a NG, finishing seventh and beaten 5 lengths. With even luck and a clean start can sneak into the finish. MY MONROE (1) is always hard to beat when drawn in this box.",
